# EC2 Basics

## EC2 Overview
- Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) provides resizable virtual machines.
- Common instance types: t3, m5, c6g (general, compute, memory optimized)
- Purchase options: On-demand, Reserved, Spot Instances

## Auto Scaling
- EC2 can be added/removed dynamically via Auto Scaling Group (ASG).
- Launch Template used to define instance config.

## Storage
- Default storage: EBS (gp3, io1, sc1)
- Optionally attach ephemeral instance store

## Monitoring
- CloudWatch for metrics and alarms
- CloudTrail for auditing EC2 API calls
